The paper deals with multi-domain task-oriented spoken dialogue systems, which are typically studied in the field of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques to model the reference resolution task, which falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments conducted in the paper involve establishing a baseline for the CQR task, which involves natural language processing and machine learning, and thus could also be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with spoken dialogue systems, which could be categorized under speech and dialogue processing (cs.SD). Finally, the paper involves query reformulation, which is a subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR).
